```
pip3 install bottle
pip3 install RPi.GPIO

# create configuration file
sudo mkdir /etc/py-smartframe/
sudo cp config.ini.sample /etc/py-smartframe/config.ini

# configure
vim /etc/py-smartframe/config.ini

# test
./py-smartframe

# configure at startup: add this line to /etc/rc.local
# nohup /path/to/py-smartframe > /dev/null &
#
# with concatenated logs: nohup /path/to/py-smartframe >> /var/log/py-smartframe.log 2>&1 &

```

## Print & delete file list

Creating the files manually is mandatory. PySmartframe won't do it for you.

> see `[files-path]` section of your configuration file

## Start Py-SmartFrame automatically

Add this line to `/etc/rc.local` file, before `exit 0` (last line)

```
nohup python3 /path/to/py-smartframe/install/directory/py-smartframe > /dev/null &
```

## Use CRON service to automatically change displayed album

Example of cron file configuration in `/etc/cron.d/py-smartframe`, with py-smartframe http server listening on `http://localhost:8080`

```
# Display random album at 6am, 1pm, 8.10pm and 10pm
06 00 * * * root curl http://localhost:8080/random/ &> /dev/null
13 00 * * * root curl http://localhost:8080/random/ &> /dev/null
22 00 * * * root curl http://localhost:8080/random/ &> /dev/null
20 10 * * * root curl http://localhost:8080/random/ &> /dev/null
```
